{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "bin_skolem_spatial_join",
    "description": "M4 schema fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §A.8 / §8.1; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.8.5; bead ess-my4.4.2): the bin-Skolem spatial-join REPRESENTATION for the conservative-regridding broad phase. The candidate overlap-pair set {(i,j)} is the spatial (theta) join of source and target cells — NOT covered by M2's equi-only join.on directly — realized as a bin-Skolem EQUI-join. DECISION (bead item 3): no new `bin`/`floor` leaf op is needed; it COMPOSES from existing ops. Each cell's coordinate is quantized to an INTEGER lat-lon bin via the existing `floor` op, a bin key is minted with `skolem`, and the candidate pairs are the landed M2 `join.on` equi-join of source and target cells sharing a bin key. Integer bin keys keep the candidate set BYTE-IDENTICAL across bindings (§5.5 / §5.8.5 determinism contract — no floating-point coordinate comparison enters the broad phase); only the post-clip per-pair area (the `intersect_polygon` narrow phase, a separate fixture) is tolerance-based. The full worked overlap-join idiom + A.8 piece-by-piece mapping is bead ess-my4.4.5; STR-tree acceleration is an explicit perf follow-on, not represented here. This is a STRUCTURAL fixture: it validates against the additive schema with no evaluator.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.furiosa"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "geometry",
      "spatial-join",
      "bin-skolem",
      "floor",
      "skolem",
      "join",
      "value-invention",
      "conformance",
      "schema",
      "ess-my4.4.2"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "BinSkolemSpatialJoin": {
      "index_sets": {
        "src_cells": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 4
        },
        "tgt_cells": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 4
        },
        "candidate_pairs": {
          "kind": "derived",
          "from_faq": "candidate_set"
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "src_lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "Source-cell representative longitude (e.g. bbox-min corner). Float coordinate — enters ONLY the integer binning via floor, never a raw join comparison."
        },
        "src_lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["src_cells"]
        },
        "tgt_lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"]
        },
        "tgt_lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"]
        },
        "dx": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Bin width in degrees — the exactly-defined integer quantization step (§5.8.5)."
        },
        "dy": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": []
        },
        "src_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["src_cells"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each source cell: skolem(\"bin\", floor(lon/dx), floor(lat/dy)). The `floor` op does the integer quantization — no bespoke binning op."
        },
        "tgt_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["tgt_cells"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each target cell — the equi-join column the candidate set joins on."
        },
        "pair_exists": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["candidate_pairs"],
          "description": "Membership over the candidate overlap-pair set produced by the bin-Skolem equi-join (the broad phase). The byte-identical integer candidate set of §5.8.5."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "Bin each SOURCE cell to an integer lat-lon bin key. floor(lon/dx) and floor(lat/dy) are integer bin coordinates (the existing `floor` op — item-3 decision: no new bin op); skolem mints the content-addressed bin key. Per-element map: output_idx [i], no contraction.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": ["src_bin", "i"]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": {
              "i": { "from": "src_cells" }
            },
            "args": ["src_lon", "src_lat", "dx", "dy"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    { "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["src_lon", "i"] }, "dx"] }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    { "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["src_lat", "i"] }, "dy"] }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "Bin each TARGET cell identically — same dx/dy quantization so a shared bin key means the bboxes fall in the same broad-phase bucket.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": ["tgt_bin", "j"]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": ["j"],
            "ranges": {
              "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" }
            },
            "args": ["tgt_lon", "tgt_lat", "dx", "dy"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    { "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["tgt_lon", "j"] }, "dx"] }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    { "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["tgt_lat", "j"] }, "dy"] }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "Candidate overlap-pair set = the bin-Skolem EQUI-join: the index-set-producing aggregate (bool_and_or, distinct:true) ranges source i and target j, the M2 `join.on` keeps only (i,j) whose bin keys are EQUAL (join on [src_bin, tgt_bin]), and skolem(\"pair\", i, j) names each surviving candidate. The `true` body marks membership. This is the landed M2 equi-join reused on integer bin keys (§5.8.5) — no spatial-index op in the IR; the index is a physical-operator/planner concern (a non-goal here).",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": ["pair_exists", "p"]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "id": "candidate_set",
            "semiring": "bool_and_or",
            "distinct": true,
            "output_idx": ["p"],
            "ranges": {
              "i": { "from": "src_cells" },
              "j": { "from": "tgt_cells" }
            },
            "join": [
              { "on": [["src_bin", "tgt_bin"]] }
            ],
            "args": ["src_bin", "tgt_bin"],
            "key": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": ["pair", "i", "j"]
            },
            "expr": {
              "op": "true",
              "args": []
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
